tweet: In April, more than 320,000 people registered for the National Campaign for Emergency Social Response for assistance due to work lost as a result of COVID-19 preventive measures, the vast majority being daily labourers. #Syria

Food insecurity remains highest in northwest Syria’s Aleppo Governorate, where large-scale internal displacement, economic decline, and the spread of COVID-19 contributed to inadequate food consumption among 57 percent of households included in the #WFP survey. #Syria #Aleppo
An inter-agency socio-economic impact assessment of COVID-19 in #Syria completed in August found that in the preceding months, an estimated 200,000-300,000 jobs had been permanently lost.
